  "prompt": "Can the same Jio SIM be used on two different mobile handsets?",
  "response": "No, a single Jio SIM card can only be actively used in one mobile handset at a time. When you move the SIM card to a different handset, the new device will become the active device for that SIM, and the previous handset will lose its mobile network connectivity. It\u2019s not possible to use one SIM card simultaneously in two different handsets. If you want to use the same mobile number on different devices, you might need to look into options like dual-SIM capable phones or call and text forwarding services.",
